    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If a company grants everyone admin rights, an intruder can easily pivot across the entire network, since every account has the same level of power. In the worst-case scenario, a single compromised credential could allow an attacker to read, modify, or delete any data, including sensitive payroll records, customer information, or critical infrastructure configurations. This lack of containment means that a breach isn't just a localized issue but a full-blown network takeover, making it significantly harder to contain and recover from the incident.",
